    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.5041/22.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Strike of Habana stevedores last night. General strike threatened unless military
                    orders 71 and 76 are enforced. Present strike seriously damages horticultural
                    interests, almost entirely American, and important American shipping interests.
                    For political reasons the Government is anxious to conciliate the stevedores,
                    and is urging shipping interests to accept their demands. In the event of
                    violence I fear the Government will not afford adequate protection without
                    strong representations from the legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
